/- A function `f` is in `L^{p, r}` if `f` is measurable and `‖f‖_{L^{p, r}} < ∞`.
The norm `‖f‖_{L^{p, r}}` is defined as `∫_0^∞ f⁻¹(x) * x^r dx / r` for `p = ∞` and `‖f‖_{L^{p, r}} = (∫_0^∞ |f(x)|^p x^r dx / r)^{1/p}` for `p < ∞`.
